headline: Chipotle Will Open Its First Asian Eateries. It Needs to Sell a Lot More Burritos Back Home, Too.
summary: The burrito maker’s expansion into Asia follows its moves into Mexico and the Mideast. The stock is down 35% year to date and is nearing its lowest level in 10 years.

headline: New CFO Appointment Might Change The Case For Investing In Sweetgreen (SG)
summary: Sweetgreen announced that Jamie McConnell will become Chief Financial Officer on September 22, 2025, succeeding longtime CFO Mitch Reback, who has retired but will remain as an advisor for six months to support the leadership transition. This transition comes as Sweetgreen seeks to reverse recent operational challenges and disappointing second quarter results, with McConnell bringing extensive leadership experience from Chipotle and other leading food and retail companies.
